Exploring Annotation

Sifan Zhang

2024-12-09

In this workflow we will compare unsupervised annotation with reference-based annotation For reference annotation we will use Azimuth pipeline guidelines can be found in Azimuth annotation

Prepare r packages

azimuth and SeuratData need to be downloaded from github, its for reference annonation. Downloading could pop up errors, just keep trying installing packages thats missing.

devtools::install_github("satijalab/seurat", "seurat5") devtools::install_github("satijalab/seurat-data", "seurat5") remotes::install_github('satijalab/azimuth', ref = 'master')

library(devtools)
library(remotes)

library(SeuratWrappers)
library(Azimuth)
library(SeuratObject)
library(Seurat)
library(Matrix)

library(cowplot)

Subcluster DCs

Note that at this point DCs cant be separated into cDC1 and cDC2, so we need to do subclustering

sub.cells <- subset(data, idents = "cDC1_cDC2")
DefaultAssay(sub.cells)<-"RNA"
f = "obj.Rdata"
if(!file.exists(f)){
  sub.cells = sub.cells %>%
  NormalizeData() %>%
  FindVariableFeatures() %>%
  ScaleData(features = c('CLEC9A','XCR1','FCER1A','CD1C')) %>%
  RunPCA(features = c('CLEC9A','XCR1','FCER1A','CD1C'))  %>%
  FindNeighbors(dims = 1:45) %>%
  FindClusters(resolution = 0.5) %>%
  RunUMAP(dims = 1:45) 
  save(sub.cells,file = f)
}
load(f)
DimPlot(sub.cells, reduction = 'umap',label = T)+NoLegend()

Compare Azimuth annotation with unsupervised annotation

If the internet connection is poor, you may need to manually download reference to working directory and install it. install.packages("tonsilref.SeuratData_2.0.0.tar.gz", repos = NULL, type = "source") Since I have two sample type (blood and lymph node), I tried two reference, PBMC and tonsil.

meta.data1 <- data_pbmc_ref@meta.data[, c("annotation", "predicted.celltype.l2")]

  rename(pbmc.predicted.celltype = predicted.celltype.l2)

metadata_long1 <- meta.data1 %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("annotation", "pbmc.predicted.celltype"), 
               names_to = "Type", values_to = "CellType") 

counts1 <- metadata_long1 %>%
  group_by(Type, CellType) %>%
  summarise(Count = n(), .groups = "drop")
